note 16. business segments
3ms businesses are organized, managed and internally grouped into segments based on differences in markets, products, technologies and services. 3m manages its operations in five business segments: industrial; safety and graphics; health care; electronics and energy; and consumer. 3ms five business segments bring together common or related 3m technologies, enhancing the development of innovative products and services and providing for efficient sharing of business resources. transactions among reportable segments are recorded at cost. 3m is an integrated enterprise characterized by substantial intersegment cooperation, cost allocations and inventory transfers. therefore, management does not represent that these segments, if operated independently, would report the operating income information shown. the difference between operating income and pre-tax income relates to interest income and interest expense, which are not allocated to business segments.
table of contents
effective in the third quarter of 2015, within the health care business segment, the company formed the oral care solutions division, which combined the former 3m espe and 3m unitek divisions.
